 Mexico’s Undesecretary for Latin America and the Caribbean Maximiliano Reyes denounced yesterday the siege and assured that talks between the foreign ministries cannot be held as long as there is an excessive political and military deployment. According to the Mexican official, his country has always chosen talks as the only way to solve the conflict and revealed that his government is willing to have a ‘formal, legal, and diplomatic communication,’ reported Wradio website. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network So far, Mexico has sent 28 diplomatic notes to solve the conflict; however, the discussion meetings were canceled continuously.